Dataset Description and Documentation
A Socially Compliant Reasoning Framework for Autonomous AI Agents in the Metaverse
Bethi Ramya Sree · Dr. Jagjit Singh Dhatterwal · Rajesh Banala · SR University, Warangal
1. Overview

This document describes all datasets used in the research paper titled “A Socially Compliant Reasoning Framework for Autonomous AI Agents in the Metaverse: Integrating Ontology-Driven Intelligence and Deep Learning.” The study employs two categories of data: (1) synthetic corpora generated specifically for this research using a Unity3D simulation environment, and (2) publicly available benchmark datasets used for training the multimodal perception and emotion recognition modules.

The three synthetic datasets correspond to the three core Metaverse evaluation scenarios described in Section 5 of the paper: virtual classroom tutoring, e-commerce negotiation, and multi-party conflict mediation. Each dataset is annotated with norm compliance scores, Social Practice Theory (SPT) labels, ontology-grounded reasoning traces, and emotion alignment metrics aligned precisely to the mathematical formulations in the paper.

