2. Synthetic Datasets (Original — Included in Repository)

The three synthetic datasets were constructed as part of this research to fill a gap in publicly available corpora: no existing dataset captures the combination of social practice annotations, ontology-grounded reasoning traces, and multi-turn emotion dynamics required to evaluate the proposed framework in Metaverse scenarios. They were generated in Unity3D, reviewed for social realism by the research team, and annotated using the SPT practice library and the norm compliance rubric described in Equation 9 of the paper.

2.1  Classroom Interactions Dataset

Description
This dataset contains turn-by-turn dialogue sessions between an AI tutor agent and student avatars in a Unity3D virtual classroom environment. Sessions span diverse subjects including mathematics, computer science, and critical thinking. The dataset is designed to evaluate the agent’s ability to apply pedagogical social practices such as scaffolded questioning, empathetic encouragement, positive reinforcement, and celebratory progression — all defined in the SPT practice library.

