2.3  Conflict Mediation Dataset

Description
This is the most socially complex dataset in the collection. It contains three-party sessions in which the AI mediator agent works to de-escalate disputes between two conflicting user avatars. Disputes span team project disagreements, workplace task allocation conflicts, and neighbour complaints. The mediator must simultaneously track the emotional states of two parties, maintain strict neutrality, apply structured mediation practices (e.g., active reflective listening, dual validation, reframing), and construct forward agreements. This scenario produces the highest emotion alignment score (0.91) and user trust (4.6) in the paper’s results, confirming that empathetic sensitivity is especially critical in high-tension environments.

