3. Public Benchmark Datasets (External — Not Included in Repository)

The following publicly available datasets were used to train the multimodal fusion encoder and emotion recognition components of the framework (Section 5 of the paper). They are not included in this repository due to their size and licensing conditions. Researchers wishing to reproduce the full training pipeline should download them from the official sources linked below.

3.1  CMU-MOSEI

Description
CMU-MOSEI (CMU Multimodal Opinion Sentiment and Emotion Intensity) is one of the largest and most widely used multimodal sentiment and emotion benchmarks in the literature. It contains video segments from YouTube, each aligned across text (transcripts), audio (prosodic features), and vision (facial action units), with fine-grained annotations for sentiment polarity and six discrete emotion categories. In this research, CMU-MOSEI was used to train the transformer-based multimodal fusion encoder (Equation 4 of the paper) and to provide emotion class labels compatible with the affect vector zᵗ used in the emotion alignment reward (Equation 10).

