3.2  PersonaChat

Description
PersonaChat is a large-scale open-domain dialogue dataset in which each conversation is grounded in a persona — a set of natural-language sentences describing a speaker’s personality and background. The dataset was designed to encourage dialogue agents to produce consistent, coherent, and personality-aware responses. In this research, PersonaChat was used to train the dialogue grounding module, providing the agent with a basis for contextually coherent and empathetically consistent language generation across the three Metaverse scenarios. The persona mechanism aligns naturally with the Social Practice Theory operationalisation in this framework, where agents are expected to behave consistently with defined roles and cultural contexts.

